solution: ```class ExamRoom {
    private TreeSet<Integer> seats;
    private int n;

    public ExamRoom(int n) {
        this.n = n;
        this.seats = new TreeSet<>();
    }

    public int seat() {
        if (seats.isEmpty()) {
            seats.add(0);
            return 0;
        }
        int maxDist = seats.first();
        int pos = 0;
        Integer prev = null;
        for (int curr : seats) {
            if (prev != null) {
                int dist = (curr - prev) / 2;
                if (dist > maxDist) {
                    maxDist = dist;
                    pos = prev + dist;
                }
            }
            prev = curr;
        }
        int lastDist = (n - 1) - seats.last();
        if (lastDist > maxDist) {
            pos = n - 1;
        }
        seats.add(pos);
        return pos;
    }

    public void leave(int p) {
        seats.remove(p);
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: seat: O(k log k), leave: O(log k) where k is the number of occupied seats
space complexity: O(k)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a TreeSet to maintain occupied seats in sorted order. seat() scans adjacent pairs to find the largest gap, handling edge gaps separately. leave() simply removes the seat. Efficient for up to 10^4 calls.

